<!-- 4.5.15 -->
<div class='toload proposition'>
	<p><span class='envidentifier'>Proposition 4.5.15</span>
	Let $G$ be a group and $\mathbf{S}(G)$ its universal inverse semigroup. Then
	<ol class='alphpar'>
		<li>
			$\mathbf{S}(G)$ is $E$-unitary (see \cite[Remark 3.5]{MR1469405}).
		</li>
		
		<li>
			The map $G\to \mathbf{G}(\mathbf{S}(G))$, $g\mapsto [[g]]$, is an isomorphism.
		</li>
	</ol>
	</p>
</div>